article.headline: Seminoles use 16-0 second-half run in win
article.linkText: No. 24 Florida State snaps two-game losing skid
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Roneeka Hodges scored 18 points and No. 24 Florida State snapped its first two-game losing streak of the season with a 73-49 win over Lipscomb on Thursday night.

Florida State (19-4) led throughout and broke the game open midway through the second half with a 16-0 run.

After Lipscomb cut the Seminoles' 14-point lead to eight, Florida State's defense held the Bisons scoreless for more than four minutes to put the game out of reach. Six Seminoles scored during that stretch.

Linnea Liljestrand added 16 points and Holly Johnson had 11 for the Seminoles, who had lost consecutive games to Miami and Virginia following the best start in school history.

Ganiyat Adeduntan grabbed 11 boards to help Florida State outrebound Lipscomb 50-27. Adeduntan also had five of the Seminoles' 13 steals.

Katie Beth Pate led Lipscomb (10-8) with 15 points.

The Seminoles shot 53 percent from the field in the first half behind 13 points from Hodges and 11 from Liljestrand. Florida State led by as many as 13 in the first half and took a 41-29 halftime lead.
